-- Western Union profit falls 4 pct as costs rise
-- 
-- Thu May 01, 2014 04:08PM EDT
-- None



May 1 (Reuters) - Western Union Co <WU.N>, the world's largest money-transfer company, reported a 4 percent fall in first-quarter profit, hurt by a rise in costs.

Net income fell to $203 million, or 37 cents per share, in the quarter ended March 31, from $212 million, or 37 cents per share, a year earlier. [ID:nBw4c3Ly6a] Total expenses rose 5 percent to $1.08 billion. Revenue rose 2 percent to $1.35 billion.